President Donald J. Trump will meet with President Uhuru Kenyatta of Kenya on August 27, 2018. The purpose of the meeting is to discuss ways to enhance the strategic partnership between the United States and Kenya based on their shared democratic values and mutual interests. The meeting will also serve to reaffirm the strong relationship between the two countries, which plays a crucial role in maintaining peace and stability in Africa and the Indo-Pacific region. Additionally, the leaders will explore opportunities to increase trade and investment while enhancing security cooperation.